						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How would you set the "PRG ROM size in 16384 byte units" and "CHR ROM size in 8192 byte units" field for Galaxian with your new mapper?<br /></div><br /><br />That depends how a specific emulator has set its rom buffer, but in simplest form I can think of is:<br /><br />saying the new mapper number is 256 for example:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">byte header&#91;16&#93; = &#123;&#125;<br />byte rom_buffer&#91;0x7FFF&#93; = &#123;&#125;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;//maps to 8000h ~ FFFFh of 6502 addr range<br /><br />getHeader&#40;header, &quot;Galaxian.nes&quot;&#41;;<br />switch &#40;translateMapper&#40;header&#41;&#41; <br />&#123;<br />...<br />case 256:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;for &#40;int i = 0; i &lt; 4; i++&#41; <br />&nbsp; &#123;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; loadBytes&#40;rom_buffer, i * 0x2000, &quot;Galaxian.nes&quot;, 16, 0x2000&#41;<br />&nbsp; &#125;<br />&#125;<br /></div><br />.................................................................................<br />a little primitive but will work, I suppose <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> <br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Alternate answer: "All iNES images are overdumps; use UNIF instead."</div> 
<br />
<br />There have been trials, but the rom listers hate UNIF header as it is very undocumented and under-maintained.  Unless more effort is put for the UNIF project by someone, I consider it pretty much a dead project. suppose.</div>

