					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">As I understand it, the definition of an iNES header doesn't say "16384*nprg bytes unless mapper is X, Y, or Z"; it says "16384*nprg bytes" full stop.<br /></div><br />The header doesn't say 16384 bytes. It only says there are X numbers of banks. The iNes header never include the bank size information. It is defaulted to 16384 by the iNes author, and if you follow this rule, it simply makes 8kB rom illegal, that's all.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You wouldn't have to convert every ROM, just the ones that can't be represented as iNES.<br /></div><br />Rom listers and collectors doesn't like that. It has to be either all NES or all UNIF. And I personally don't like using two standardized formats for one kind of system, either. It looks very messy.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Besides, even if you want a 100% Pure UNIF collection, that's more the job of a ROM auditing tool similar to GoodNES: for each SHA1(PRG) and SHA1(CHR), it would store the correct UNIF chunks for this dump.<br /></div><br />Every rom auditing tool needs a DAT file to fix a collection. Somebody must manually edit 3000+ NES roms header and create UNIF headered collection before anybody can take advantage of these auditing tools you are talking about. Rom auditing tools can be good but they never are  MAGIC.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Futhermore, assigning a new iNes mapper number doesn't have any effect on the board type declaration of UNIF header. If you don't like iNes header in the first place, why do you mind whether iNes mappers are being wasted or not?</div>
<br />Again the total number of iNes mappers can be increased up to 2048 mappers if we are going to use the lower nibble of 7th byte of iNES header. This will be more than plenty for the all the new dumps that you can imagine of,  plus all the pokemon that you can catch.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

